<dl id="n01060f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01060f">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01060f"> 60(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> her face positively / burning</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">His gentle manner was inexpressibly soothing. It was so soothing that just as he was leaving she kept him back with a gesture. <p>&ldquo;Doctor, before you go, I wish you would do something for me.&rdquo; And she sat down, <mark>her face positively burning</mark>, and shed tears.</p> <small> Arnold Bennett, <a name="ABNL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ABNL"><cite title="source">Lilian</cite></a>, (1922) 240 [197]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05130a" href="c05all.htm#c05130a">VI.C.05:130(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
